[{"id":"a92b54ec1dd5ac00e37187c6feafe829","from":"Lookout Mobile Security","from_email":"feedback@email.lookout.com","to":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","to_list":[{"name":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"Don\u2019t be a ransomware victim | Tips to stay safe","date":"2016-06-13T16:07:48.000Z","formatted_date":"Jun 13, 2016","formatted_time":"4:07 PM","body":" \n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=a7f3b016eb729ce2e3d385d9ee111419f133ac5363aa1b23d1d161d712d91359e2cae0eb4b2f5a93 \n\nMobile ransomware locks your device and demands you pay money to gain access again. Attackers are betting that you value your device and the information on it enough to pay.\n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=a7f3b016eb729ce285f571343359497426dcd2986a4deca0af7ec8f60637fff5b517a8d8d9c894b6 \nCheck for Malware \n\nDon't be fooled by ransomware\n\n\n\nAvoid ransomware by taking steps to proactively secure your phone:\n\n\n.;\n\n Learn about \u201cdevice administrator\u201d and be careful of what apps you give this permission. \n\n\n.;\n\nDon't download apps from third party marketplaces\n\n\n.;\n\nRegularly backup your data\n\n\n.;\n\nUse a security app, like Lookout, that will let you know if something is amiss\n\n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=a7f3b016eb729ce2e3d385d9ee111419f133ac5363aa1b23d1d161d712d91359e2cae0eb4b2f5a93 \nOpen Lookout \n\nFor more on mobile ransomware and how you can stay safe, check out the first chapter in our \"Why Mobile Security Matters\" blog series. \nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=a7f3b016eb729ce2a107688552f5b2b8ee39053db514503d5024573287fa4b315ea7bdfb5c48bc2a \nRead the blog .\n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=a7f3b016eb729ce2f3d95ff1a20a0d0a78f470239561405b5d153e157359e839203e0df09dc39a1e \n\nhttps://click.email.lookout.com/?qs=a7f3b016eb729ce2921c088a4dfb4f4db29a341f0c4e17c50c397b4d657b547f0b94397291ca91c3 \n\n\nSent from Lookout, Inc.\n\n\n1 Front Street Suite 2700\n\n\nSan Francisco, CA 94111\n\n\n